---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LessonNav from '../../components/LessonNav.astro';
import LessonAudio from '../../components/LessonAudio.astro';
---
<Layout title="Lesson 5: Design Process Documentation">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <span class="lesson-badge">Lesson 5</span>
    <h1>Design Process Documentation</h1>
    <p class="lesson-subtitle">How to show judges your team's engineering journey from start to finish.</p>
    <LessonAudio slug="lesson-3" />
  </div>

  <p>
    The <strong>design process</strong> section is usually one of the highest-weighted parts of 
    your portfolio. This is where you show judges how your team went from identifying a problem to actually solving it.
  </p>

  <h2>The Engineering Design Process</h2>
  <p>Engineers everywhere use this process to solve complex problems step by step. What matters for your portfolio is showing how your team actually applied it throughout the season to improve your robot.</p>
  <p>Here's the process:</p>
  
  <div class="process-steps">
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">1</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Define</strong>
        <p>What problem are you solving?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">2</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Research</strong>
        <p>What solutions already exist?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">3</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Brainstorm</strong>
        <p>What can we do to solve this?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">4</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Prototype</strong>
        <p>Can this be built in real life?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">5</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Test</strong>
        <p>How does this perform under real conditions?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">6</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Iterate</strong>
        <p>How can this be improved?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Problem Definition</h2>
  <p>Start by clearly stating the challenge you're addressing:</p>
  
  <blockquote>
    Our robot needs to launch game elements 54 inches high while staying within the 18" x 18" x 18" starting size constraint.
  </blockquote>

  <p>Include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Game requirements</li>
    <li>Constraints (size, weight, rules)</li>
    <li>Success criteria</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Iterations</h2>
  <p>Document multiple design ideas, not just the final one. Create a graph, decision matrix, or table to compare results:</p>
  
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Iteration</th>
        <th>Simplicity</th>
        <th>Reliability</th>
        <th>Efficiency</th>
        <th>Total</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>V1</td>
        <td>5</td>
        <td>4</td>
        <td>6</td>
        <td><strong>15/30</strong></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>V2</td>
        <td>7</td>
        <td>6</td>
        <td>8</td>
        <td><strong>21/30</strong></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>V3</td>
        <td>9</td>
        <td>8</td>
        <td>9</td>
        <td><strong>26/30</strong></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Document Your Iterations With Measurable Outcomes</h2>
  <p>Don't just show different versions - back up your design changes with <strong>real data</strong>. Track actual metrics across your iterations so you can prove each change made a measurable difference. This turns your design story from "we tried a bunch of stuff" into "we systematically improved performance."</p>

  <h3>Example: Tracking Shooting Time Across the Season</h3>
  <p>Here's how you could document iteration outcomes with real performance data. By measuring shooting cycle time at each competition, you can show judges the direct impact of your design changes:</p>
  
  <div class="graph-container">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 650 350" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="progress-graph">
      <!-- Grid lines -->
      <line x1="90" y1="280" x2="620" y2="280" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="2"/>
      <line x1="90" y1="30" x2="90" y2="280" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="2"/>
      
      <!-- Y-axis labels (time in seconds) -->
      <text x="80" y="285" font-size="12" text-anchor="end" fill="var(--text-muted)">0s</text>
      <text x="80" y="245" font-size="12" text-anchor="end" fill="var(--text-muted)">2.5s</text>
      <text x="80" y="205" font-size="12" text-anchor="end" fill="var(--text-muted)">5s</text>
      <text x="80" y="165" font-size="12" text-anchor="end" fill="var(--text-muted)">7.5s</text>
      <text x="80" y="125" font-size="12" text-anchor="end" fill="var(--text-muted)">10s</text>
      
      <!-- Horizontal grid lines -->
      <line x1="90" y1="240" x2="620" y2="240" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4"/>
      <line x1="90" y1="200" x2="620" y2="200" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4"/>
      <line x1="90" y1="160" x2="620" y2="160" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4"/>
      <line x1="90" y1="120" x2="620" y2="120" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4"/>
      
      <!-- Data points and line -->
      <polyline points="130,30 220,57.5 310,205 400,242.5 490,267.5" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      
      <!-- Data point circles -->
      <circle cx="130" cy="30" r="5" fill="var(--accent)"/>
      <circle cx="220" cy="57.5" r="5" fill="var(--accent)"/>
      <circle cx="310" cy="205" r="5" fill="var(--accent)"/>
      <circle cx="400" cy="242.5" r="5" fill="var(--accent)"/>
      <circle cx="490" cy="267.5" r="5" fill="var(--accent)"/>
      
      <!-- X-axis labels (meets) -->
      <text x="130" y="310" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-muted)">LM1</text>
      <text x="220" y="310" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-muted)">LM2</text>
      <text x="310" y="310" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-muted)">LT</text>
      <text x="400" y="310" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-muted)">SQ</text>
      <text x="490" y="310" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-muted)">CMP</text>
      
      <!-- Axis labels -->
      <text x="355" y="340" font-size="13" font-weight="600" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-secondary)">Competition Timeline</text>
      <text x="10" y="150" font-size="13" font-weight="600" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text-secondary)" transform="rotate(-90 10 150)">Shooting Time (seconds)</text>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <p><strong>What This Shows:</strong> Starting at 10 seconds per 3 artifacts shot at LM1, we made <em>minimal improvements</em> by LM2 (9.5s). However, between LM2 and League Tournament we achieved a major breakthrough, dropping to 3 seconds through a fundamental design change. Continued optimization led to 1.5 seconds at Semifinals and finally 0.5 seconds at State.</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>LM1 (10s):</strong> Initial design with static launch</li>
    <li><strong>LM2 (9.5s):</strong> Minor tuning of PIDF</li>
    <li><strong>LT (3s):</strong> Added a second motor to the flywheel</li>
    <li><strong>SQ (1.5s):</strong> Implemented automated firing sequence</li>
    <li><strong>CMP (0.5s):</strong> Increased flywheel weights</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Why Judges Care:</strong> This kind of documentation proves you understand the connection between <em>design decisions</em> and <em>actual results</em>. It shows real problem-solving, not just luck. Numbers are always stronger than vague descriptions.</p>

  <h2>Document Your Iterations</h2>
  <p>Show your iterative process with each version:</p>
  
  <div class="iteration-cards">
    <div class="iteration">
      <span class="iter-label">v1</span>
      <h4>First Prototype</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>What you built</li>
        <li>What you tested</li>
        <li>Problems encountered</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="iteration">
      <span class="iter-label">v2</span>
      <h4>Second Iteration</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Changes made</li>
        <li>New test results</li>
        <li>Improvements observed</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="iteration">
      <span class="iter-label">v3</span>
      <h4>Final Design</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Final refinements</li>
        <li>Performance metrics</li>
        <li>Why you're confident</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout tip">
    <strong><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="display: inline-block; vertical-align: -0.15em; margin-right: 0.25em;"><path d="M15 14c.2-1 .7-1.7 1.5-2.5 1-.9 1.5-2.2 1.5-3.5A6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 1 .2 2.2 1.5 3.5.7.7 1.3 1.5 1.5 2.5"></path><path d="M9 18h6"></path><path d="M10 22h4"></path></svg>Data is King:</strong> Use quantitative data whenever possible. Instead of 
    "The intake worked well," write "The intake had an 80% success rate with an average cycle time of 2.3 seconds."
  </div>

  <LessonNav 
    prev={{ title: "Team Overview", href: "/lessons/lesson-4/" }}
    next={{ title: "CAD & Technical Drawings", href: "/lessons/lesson-5/" }}
  />
</Layout>

<style>
  .process-steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface-solid);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .step-num {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .step strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .step p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .iteration-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .iteration {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface-solid);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .iter-label {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    background: var(--accent-faint);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .iteration h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .iteration ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .graph-container {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface-solid);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .progress-graph {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    min-height: 350px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .process-steps {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
    
    .iteration-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .process-steps {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
